# Hostinger VPS (Ubuntu) — fix 413 on file uploads
#
# Symptom: KYC, tickets, any multipart upload works locally but returns
#          413 Content Too Large on https://api.betabase.pro
#
# Cause: nginx default client_max_body_size is 1MB.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# QUICK FIX (SSH into VPS, then run):
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   cd /var/www/betabase   # or your project path
#   git pull
#   sudo bash BE/deploy/fix-nginx-uploads.sh
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MANUAL FIX
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Find API nginx config:
#      sudo grep -r "api.betabase" /etc/nginx/
#
# 2. Edit that file (sites-enabled or sites-available):
#      sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/api.betabase.pro
#
# 3. Inside BOTH server { } blocks (port 80 AND 443 if SSL), add:
#
#      client_max_body_size 55m;
#      client_body_timeout 120s;
#
# 4. Inside location / { } that proxy_passes to Node, also add:
#
#      proxy_read_timeout 120s;
#      proxy_send_timeout 120s;
#
# 5. Test and reload:
#      sudo nginx -t
#      sudo systemctl reload nginx
#
# 6. Restart Node backend:
#      pm2 restart all
#      # or: cd BE && npm start
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CERTBOT / HTTPS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# certbot often creates a NEW server { listen 443 ssl; } block.
# You MUST add client_max_body_size 55m; to the HTTPS block too,
# not only port 80.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLOUDFLARE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# If api.betabase.pro is proxied (orange cloud), uploads up to ~100MB
# are usually fine. 413 with nginx HTML body = nginx on VPS, not CF.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VERIFY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   curl -I https://api.betabase.pro/api/v1/getLinks
#   grep client_max_body_size /etc/nginx/conf.d/00-betabase-upload-limits.conf
#
# See also: nginx-api.betabase.pro.conf (full site example)
